						               													<description>Game Background:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You are the leader of a village in the forest of Na~TACE. Your expansion views require resources and pushes you to explore the surrounding areas.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Your lumberer will quickly discover areas for the development of agriculture for your farmers or mining for your blacksmith.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The wood harvested and will allow you to build farms, forges, fences or barracks for your soldiers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;But will your farmers and your hunter be able to provide enough food for your soldiers? No problem, send your merchant to other villages to share valuable resources.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Many other surprises await you in this game of resources gathering, war and colonization.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Finally, attack enemy villages to colonize the entire forest and win the game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal of the game is to eliminated other players by destroying their village with your soldiers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;24, 36 or 48 hexa cards (forests) are placed in a predetermined shape according to the number of players.&amp;#10;Each player choose a village and pick 3 ressources card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Player 1 will advance his lumberer pawn forest by forest and discover 3 areas by flipping the forests he passes on. Underneath, he may discover a regular forest, a farm land, a mind land or a special land.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The lumberer will pick 3 wood cards and will use them to build farms (placing a pawn on the farm land), mines (placing a pawn on the mine land) or barracks (placing a pawn on the village).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For each farmer, the player will pick 1 farm card per farm land with a farmer. The food will be use to feed the soldiers (1 per barrack). Soldier pawns will be moved and advance to eventually attack the other villages or soldiers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a soldier or a group of soldiers attack, a D6 is used + all bonus cards the attacker player may have collect. Defense is fixed by the number of soldiers or what type of building is attacked + any defensive bonus the defendant player may have gathered.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
